 told Reuters.\n\n&#x200B;\n\nLooking into Omnicom Group Q4 2019 [earnings report.](http://s2.q4cdn.com/400719266/files/doc_financials/2019/q4/2019-12-31-Omnicom-Group-Earnings-Release.pdf)\n\nTheir revenue for 2019 was $14,953,000,000 already down from $15,290,000,000 in 2018.\n\nWith a salary and service cost of $10,972,000,000 and net income of $1,339,000,000.That's a whole lot of salaries to pay. Looks like we're going to see a lot of layoffs.\n\n&#x200B;\n\nI suspect their revenue streams are going to dry up quickly with a lot of big brands pulling out of contracts all year around.\n\n&#x200B;\n\n[Bought all that i could.  ](https://preview.redd.it/s1tt78vs8un41.jpg?width=737&format=pjpg&auto=webp&s=4278435bc41f1795fdce4585bf4da5eb537f11c4)\n\n**TL;DR $OMC 4/17 50p**", "created_utc": 1584715200.0, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/flw34h/dd_marketing_agencies_are_going_to_crunch_hard/", "is_self": true}